shared_text:
Clarendon School District Two
August 28 at 2:34 PM ·

Greetings, CSD2 Family!

The Office of School Nutrition Services will be providing meals to students enrolled in Clarendon School District Two beginning September 11, 2020. This survey will provide information on how to prepare for feeding students participating in the hybrid model as well as those who will be learning virtually.

You must submit a new survey for each enrolled student in your household.

As a part of the USDA requirements, each child will have a School Issued Meal Number to collect their meals. Be sure to include your email address to receive follow-up information specific to your student and their Meal Number.

We will be sending this survey out in a variety of platforms; however, you only need to complete it once per child.

If you have any questions or concerns, please contact Tonia Smith at tmsmith@csd2.org or 803.825.5134.

Thank You!!

(Click on the link below to complete the survey.)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScT3VMVUeeOIym1S-zj4cL5XyMD6y_gVw5a63zuie1by_0Fcg/viewform

post_text:
IMPORTANT UPDATE REGARDING STUDENT ATTENDANCE!!!

Students will be counted as 'present' as long as they complete the day's assignment(s) by 11:59pm. Teachers will take attendance, daily, of the students who logged into class for the live session. If students aren't present for their live sessions, they will be marked 'absent'; however, if they complete their assignment(s) for the day before 11:59pm, the teacher needs to provide the school's PowerSchool person with a list of the students whose absence needs to be changed to present, because teachers will no longer be able to make those changes, themselves, after 11:59pm.

Hello Clarendon Two Family,

Our scheduled LEAP Days have changed in response to the possibilities of inclement weather in our area. The safety of our students, parents, staff, and school communities are of utmost importance to us.

Our scheduled LEAP Days will be delayed for one day. Monday’s Students will now be scheduled for this Friday. All other students will remain on their scheduled days on Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday.

Please continue checking for updates of attendance for students on our district’s website, Facebook page, and school websites. Thank you for your attention to this message, stay safe and we hope you have a nice evening.

#WeAreMonarchs
#MonarchStrong

post_text:
Montessori Applications

CSD2 Families: We are now accepting applications for our Montessori program for the 2020-2021 school year. Applications will be accepted between June 22-July 2, 2020. Please take time to review our Montessori Fact sheet before completing your application. Applications must be received between the time frame of June 22-July 2, 2020, and be completed on the new template (electronically or hard copy) in order to be considered.

Montessori Updates

1. Parents need to complete the new 2020-2021 Montessori application for students who are currently enrolled in Montessori classes.

2. Parents who completed Montessori applications in the Spring, after orientations, still need to complete the new 2020-2021 application, as well.

Click the link below to complete the 2020-2021 Montessori Application.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSefG_5_69lpSG_bRhAktvxVlwhMjRyFIRWjceF-Vb8u6pYbfA/viewform?usp=sf_link

Clarendon School District Two Offers Grab-And-Go Meals

Dear Clarendon School District Two Families:

We know that many of you have been consistently participating in the Grab and Go Meal Program during this difficult time. Due to some parents returning back to work, we’ve noticed that lesser parents are showing up to pick up Grab and Go Meals. With that being said, we want to determine, for meal preparation purposes, the level of service we may need to provide from June 8 to June 30, 2020.

Please complete the Google form https://forms.gle/kcew4UUQWCCzpnW16 to assist us in this process.

Your assistance in this endeavor is greatly appreciated and we thank you for your cooperation. Should you have any questions, please contact the Food Service Department at 803-435-4082 or by email at ealfano@csd2.org.

Thank you,
Emelina Alfano
Director of Food Service

Congratulations to the Manning High School FFA!!!
#WeAreMonarchs
shared_text:
Manning FFA
May 19 at 9:19 PM ·

We received the Gold Emblem National Chapter Award along with the 100+ percent membership Award. Receiving the recognition of Gold Emblem Chapter shows that The Manning High School’s FFA Chapter is one of top chapters in the State of South Carolina. The National Chapter Award Program is designed to recognize FFA chapters that actively implement the mission and strategies of the organization. These chapters improve chapter operations using the National Quality Chapter Standards and a Program of Activities that emphasize growing leaders, building communities and strengthening agriculture. Chapters are rewarded for providing educational experiences for the entire membership. We appreciate all of our members for helping us reach this great achievement💙💛💙💛

post_text:
Clarendon School District Two will observe Spring Break on next week, April 13-17, 2020!

CSD2 family, your hard-work, commitment, and dedication to our profession, schools, students, and school communities are appreciated and has not gone unrecognized! Your response to the Coronavirus pandemic proves just how resilient you, as Monarchs, truly are!

CSD2 parents and guardians, thank you for your patience and perseverance during this time of uncertainty and constant change. Please know that we are committed to providing your children with the best possible distance learning experience. If you have any questions or need any additional support, please do not hesitate to contact your child’s teachers, school administrators, and/or district administrators, because we are here to support you!

Please use your Spring Break to rest, relax, and to safely enjoy your family and friends. Again, thank you all for your unwavering commitment to our mission of “Educating Students” and HAPPY SPRING BREAK!

We are #MONARCHSTRONG!

Attention All Parents and Guardians,

CSD2 Principals are at the schools each Monday from 8:00am – 3:00pm for you to pick up work packets for your child, if you do not have internet access. Students that have internet access are reminded to log in to Google Classroom to complete their assignments.

Teachers will be at the schools on Monday, March 30th from 9:00am – 3:00pm for you to return work packets that your child has completed and to pick up additional work. If you need to pick up work for your child before this date, please reach out to your child’s teacher and/or principal and we will work to have a packet for your child during Grab & Go Meal distribution at Manning Elementary School. Grab & Go Meals are provided Monday - Friday from 9:30am to 11:30am at MES.

As we embark upon providing new instruction for our students, we will distribute devices to students as needed.

Thanks for your support during this time!

- Avoid skin-to-skin contact with other people
- Stay home and away from others while you are sick
- Cover your mouth and nose when coughing or sneezing. And finally,
- Clean frequently touched objects and surfaces.

For more information, visit scdhec.gov/COVID19.

***Monarch Fan Bus***

February 24th - Varsity Manning Girls will take on May River High School, Bluffton SC at 7:00 P.M. The bus will depart from Manning High School between 4:00p.m. and 4:30p.m. Travel time is approximately 2 1/2 hours to May River High School in Bluffton. Cost is $21.00.

February 25th - Varsity Manning Boys will take on Cheraw High School, Cheraw SC at 7:00 P.M. The bus will depart from Manning High School between 5:00p.m. and 5:30p.m. Travel time is approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours to Cheraw High School in Cheraw. Cost is $21.00.

***No student under the age of 18 will be able to travel without their parent/guardian on the bus with them. This is a charter bus and there are only 54 seats available on a first-come basis. Deadline for payment is Monday, February 24th at 1:00p.m. Money should be paid to Beth Rollins at Manning High School to secure your seat ticket. For any additional information, please call 803-825-5045.

PLEASE NOTE: You will pay your own admission fee at the destination. Your payment is only for your bus trip to and from the game.

November 10, 2019 at 5:03 PM ·

In South Carolina, a School Improvement Council is an advisory council to the principal and school on issues related to school improvement. By law, every K-12 public school in South Carolina must have an SIC that is made up of parent, teacher, student (grades 9-12), and community member representatives. The principal is an ex-officio member of every SIC. SIC will meet once a month and 2x in January to focus on school improvements.

Nominations are being accepted for Parent positions on the SIC for MHS. Parents will serve for two years. Please send parent nominations to pgoldsmith@csd2.org by Tuesday, November 12th 5pm. Parents must have students currently enrolled at MHS. Parents may nominate themselves. Voting will take place on Wednesday, November 13th. There are four parent positions available. Thank you in advance.

post_text: Bonnie Trulsen, Librarian at Manning High School, was awarded $1,000 from Santee Electric Cooperative. Ms. Trulsen applied for their Bright Ideas Grant with the proposal Full STEAM Ahead with KEVA Planks. These blocks will be part of the library’s makerspace. The teacher librarian will collaborate with classroom teachers to provide a variety of hands on opportunities/challenges for our students to learn about science, engineering, mathematics, and art. KEVA planks are an exceptionally versatile tool to integrate STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Art, Mathematics) concepts to students of all ages and skill levels. These are wooden planks that are uniform in size that can be used for an endless number of creative projects. Planks are assembled using various stacking techniques. Construction progresses quickly so multiple trials or experiments can be conducted in the course of any challenge. Trial and error maximizes discovery and learning.

shared_text:
Clarendon School District Two added 3 new photos — at Clarendon County Sheriff's Office.
October 24, 2019 at 3:45 PM · Manning, SC ·

The Clarendon County Sheriff's Office is excited to observe Red Ribbon Week with all of our Clarendon County Schools. Red Ribbon Week is an alcohol, tobacco, and other drug and violence prevention awareness campaign observed annually in October in the United States. Students conducted experiments using different stimuli like light, moisture, sound, etc... and recorded the earthworm's response to each stimulus. After students have conducted their experiments, the earthworms will be donated to the Manning Primary STEM Lab. MPS has a "Mr. Wiggles Earthworm Farm" that students are maintaining so they can raise healthy, happy earthworms! Compost from Mr. Wiggles Earthworm Farm is used to fertilize outdoor gardens throughout the district. **Special Note** The earthworms were not harmed during the 6th grade experiments.

shared_text:
Manning High School Student Council
October 20, 2019 at 12:26 PM ·

Congratulations to our Student Body President; Jessica Salinas who continues to break barriers by becoming the FIRST Latina Homecoming Queen at Manning High School!!! 🤩 When asked what this moment meant for her, Jessica said “It felt amazing to represent the small Latino community at MHS. Even more so to know that small acts of kindness go a long way and hard work pays off. My little sister Madison has definitely been my inspiration! I hope that my older sisters Lesley, Heidi, & I will continue to be good role models for her. I want ALL young girls to know that Dreams come true, but it all depends on you!“

post_text: To help parents address questions children may have about their math homework, we have provided the Eureka Math Parent Tip Sheets for Grades K through 6. The tip sheets are available on the Clarendon School District Two website under the I AM....Parent tab. Tip sheets provide an overview of each topic and include suggested strategies and models, key vocabulary, connections to previous learning, and tips for how you can support your child's learning at home. Tips Sheets are arranged in the same sequence as the student's homework, making it easy for parents to follow along with their child's progress.

Manning High School
October 10, 2019 at 9:09 PM ·

Manning High FFA has been busy! This past weekend they assisted the Manning Lions Club with their Candy Day Friday and Saturday. This event helps with the Lions Club’s Fight for Sight Fundraiser. They also helped host the Clarendon Pilot Club’s Walk for Brain Health. MHS FFA was one of the sponsors for this event which brings awareness to brain diseases like Alzheimer’s. Saturday evening, MHS FFA assisted with the setting up and serving of dinner at the 8th Annual Breast Cancer Awareness Think Pink Banquet. Then, Manning FFA held its Honorary Dinner at MJHS Monday night. The honorees were Mrs. Terrie Ard, Mrs. Doreen Reu & Mr. Eric Blackwell. Excellent job FFA! Way to represent Manning High!

A Walmart Community Grant was awarded to Manning High School Librarian, Bonnie Trulsen. The $825 dollars will be used purchase KEVA Planks which are an exceptionally versatile tool to integrate STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Art, Mathematics) concepts to students of all skill levels. The MHS library’s makerspace provides materials to give hands on opportunities/challenges for our students to learn about science, engineering, mathematics, and art. Teacher/Librarian collaboration makes us stronger!

A big thank you to the Manning Walmart #1017 for giving back to our community.
